                             <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.8rem;">Trendlines refer to a sequence of lines and curves that are used in technical analysis to identify price patterns.
                                 Traders can use this tool to spot support and resistance on a stock price chart.</p>

                                <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.8rem;">Individuals who choose this Stock Market trend analysis strategy enter long positions when the equity shares of any company are trending higher.
                                     Moreover, this method involves placing a stop-loss order below the resistance or support levels, i.e., the key trendline. </p>
